are connected

34:02.832 --> 34:07.087
to a significant loss or trauma

34:07.170 --> 34:08.255
at an early age.

34:10.507 --> 34:13.092
Does that resonate with you?

34:13.176 --> 34:14.469
No.

34:14.552 --> 34:18.014
Hmm.

34:18.098 --> 34:20.934
Are you familiar with EMDR?

34:21.016 --> 34:22.978
No.

34:23.061 --> 34:25.063
It's an old form of therapy.

34:25.146 --> 34:28.942
Nobody really understands
why it works or how,

34:29.025 --> 34:31.277
but it does.

34:31.360 --> 34:33.487
There's something
almost magical about it.

34:34.697 --> 34:37.284
Mm. You don't believe in magic?

34:37.367 --> 34:38.034
No.

34:38.118 --> 34:43.206
Maybe that's why
you have such...

34:43.290 --> 34:45.166
trouble with love.

34:47.668 --> 34:50.130
Would you like to try EMDR?

34:50.213 --> 34:54.009
J‐Just to see if we can get
a little closer

34:54.092 --> 34:58.305
to understanding why you came.

35:00.724 --> 35:04.561
Sure. Why not?

35:04.644 --> 35:06.688
Excellent.

35:06.771 --> 35:09.524
I record all my sessions.
Do you mind?

35:11.651 --> 35:13.862
And this is just

35:13.945 --> 35:17.616
our standard release form.

35:20.452 --> 35:21.453
It's on paper.

35:21.536 --> 35:23.788
I know. What can I say?

35:23.872 --> 35:25.749
I am nostalgic
for the analog world.

35:25.832 --> 35:29.252
I suspect you are, too.

35:30.128 --> 35:32.964
Well, take a moment,
read it through.

35:33.048 --> 35:35.091
What's the date?

35:35.175 --> 35:36.718
Oh, don't worry about that.

35:36.801 --> 35:37.601
I just need your signature.

35:40.972 --> 35:44.684
Okay. Thank you.

35:44.768 --> 35:46.144
So...

35:46.227 --> 35:49.230
the way EMDR works.

35:50.523 --> 35:54.694
We pick one specific
traumatic event

35:54.778 --> 35:56.321
and then we basically
rewrite the script

35:56.404 --> 36:00.700
so it doesn't trigger
the same debilitating response.

36:00.784 --> 36:01.993
Does that make sense?
Good.

36:02.077 --> 36:07.540
We can start
on any memory, really.

36:07.624 --> 36:10.877
Is there a moment, a...

36:10.960 --> 36:14.047
a night where you remember this,

36:14.130 --> 36:17.008
as you say, "inability to love"

36:17.092 --> 36:19.010
really manifesting itself,

36:19.094 --> 36:21.429
impeding your life in some way?

36:24.974 --> 36:26.726
I...

36:28.478 --> 36:32.232
I had a fight
with my boyfriend recently.

36:32.315 --> 36:34.609
Excellent.

36:34.693 --> 36:38.738
That is the perfect thing
to unpack with this therapy.

36:38.822 --> 36:40.156
Let's start there.

36:40.240 --> 36:44.577
Can you please, um,
move your chair

36:44.661 --> 36:45.870
to face me.

36:48.665 --> 36:51.501
Good.

36:54.629 --> 36:57.882
No, see, you need to be
a little closer.

36:57.966 --> 37:01.761
There you go.

37:01.845 --> 37:03.471
Okay, to begin,

37:03.555 --> 37:07.058
just follow my fingers
with your eyes.

37:11.104 --> 37:13.565
‐Th‐That makes me dizzy.
‐Okay.

37:13.648 --> 37:17.402
Let's switch to something else.

37:19.362 --> 37:21.448
Your palms up.

37:21.531 --> 37:23.366
There you go.

37:26.453 --> 37:30.957
Close your eyes
and take a deep breath.

37:35.295 --> 37:37.964
Now think back
to the night of the fight.

37:38.047 --> 37:41.551
What do you notice?

37:41.634 --> 37:42.434
Where are you?

37:45.138 --> 37:46.973
I'm in my apartment.

37:47.056 --> 37:49.434
‐Where is that?
‐Montauk.

37:51.478 --> 37:53.521
How about your boyfriend,
is he there?

37:53.605 --> 37:54.856
He's on his way.

37:54.939 --> 37:58.067
How do you feel?

37:58.151 --> 38:00.320
Scared.

38:00.403 --> 38:02.906
Good. Go with that.

38:04.908 --> 38:07.911
Same as before.

38:07.994 --> 38:12.457
Tell me...
what do you notice?

38:12.540 --> 38:16.836
My apartment is warm, cozy.

38:16.920 --> 38:19.339
There's a fire in the fireplace.

38:19.422 --> 38:22.217
My daughter's drawings

38:22.300 --> 38:25.220
are on the refrigerator.

38:25.303 --> 38:27.430
It's raining outside.

38:27.514 --> 38:32.894
Pouring, actually.
There's a storm, a... a bad one.

38:32.977 --> 38:33.853
The windows are rattling.

38:33.937 --> 38:36.022
Good. Go with that.

38:36.105 --> 38:40.193
Now what do you see happening?

38:40.276 --> 38:42.529
My boyfriend arrives.

38:42.612 --> 38:45.532
He's soaking wet.
He dries himself by the fire.

38:45.615 --> 38:47.200
How's he dressed?

38:47.283 --> 38:50.119
Jeans and a military jacket.

38:50.203 --> 38:52.997
He's a veteran.

38:53.081 --> 38:53.748
Good.

38:53.832 --> 38:56.960
Close your eyes.

38:57.043 --> 39:00.922
Notice what he says

39:01.005 --> 39:02.382
and go with that.

39:02.465 --> 39:05.677
‐He's angry.
‐Why is he angry?

39:05.760 --> 39:08.179
Because he's married,

39:08.263 --> 39:12.100
and I want him
to leave his wife.

39:12.183 --> 39:13.935
We have a fight.

39:14.018 --> 39:16.771
I tell him that if he doesn't
leave her, I will kill myself.

39:16.855 --> 39:18.398
Keep going.

39:18.481 --> 39:20.817
He tells me that
I'm ugly and stupid

39:20.900 --> 39:22.068
and that nobody
will ever love me,

39:22.151 --> 39:25.530
and that the best I could hope
for is to be someone's slut.

39:25.613 --> 39:27.740
Okay. That's enough.

39:29.659 --> 39:32.537
EMDR doesn't work
if you're lying.

39:44.215 --> 39:47.218
I never said those things.

39:47.302 --> 39:49.596
I respected your mother greatly.

39:52.098 --> 39:55.101
I would never have
spoken that way to her.

40:08.531 --> 40:10.074
Hello, Joanie.

40:10.158 --> 40:11.618
Hello, Ben.

40:14.203 --> 40:16.581
I'm so glad
you are finally here.

40:21.210 --> 40:24.088
Why don't we start again
with the same question?

40:24.172 --> 40:26.758
How can I help you?

40:31.220 --> 40:33.765
Did you kill my mother?

40:37.810 --> 40:40.480
Yes.

40:40.563 --> 40:42.190
I did.

40:50.239 --> 40:54.160
I can only imagine
what you think of me right now.

40:54.243 --> 40:55.870
It's all so new for you.

40:58.623 --> 41:01.834
The truth is, I've been
thinking about you for years.

41:01.918 --> 41:06.214
I've tried to imagine where
you've been living your life

41:06.297 --> 41:07.799
and‐and how.

41:07.882 --> 41:12.220
I've awaited our reunion
with great anticipation.

41:16.307 --> 41:20.603
Is there anything else
you want to ask me?

41:20.687 --> 41:23.356
Anything at all?

41:23.439 --> 41:26.859
Go back behind your desk.
I need a barrier between us.

41:26.943 --> 41:29.779
Of course.

41:37.328 --> 41:40.164
I‐I want to be held
accountable, Joanie.

41:40.248 --> 41:41.833
I've always known
I would eventually

41:41.916 --> 41:44.711
have to answer for what I did.

41:44.794 --> 41:48.423
I welcome the opportunity.

41:51.676 --> 41:55.805
I know this might be hard
for you to believe,

41:55.888 --> 42:00.893
but I think of your mother
every day.

42:00.977 --> 42:03.396
Every minute, in fact.

42:03.479 --> 42:07.859
She is constantly with me,

42:07.942 --> 42:10.403
and...

42:10.486 --> 42:13.656
I hate myself for what I did.

42:13.740 --> 42:15.908
Okay. So why did you do it?

42:18.036 --> 42:20.079
I had a psychotic break.

42:20.163 --> 42:21.247
What?

42:21.330 --> 42:24.250
When I met your mother...

42:24.333 --> 42:26.753
the doctors at the VA
had me on a lot of drugs.

42:26.836 --> 42:28.921
Antidepressants, MDMA,

42:29.005 --> 42:31.257
antipsychotics.

42:31.340 --> 42:33.885
I was losing my mind.

42:33.968 --> 42:37.930
I couldn't sleep.
Uh, I‐I‐I was paranoid.

42:38.014 --> 42:39.640
I started hearing voices.

42:39.724 --> 42:42.477
I didn't tell anyone,
of course, because...

42:42.560 --> 42:45.521
I, I was afraid
they'd lock me up for good.

42:45.605 --> 42:50.610
That night...
I became a monster,

42:50.693 --> 42:53.154
uh, completely out of control.

42:54.280 --> 42:56.616
What did you do to her?

42:56.699 --> 42:58.951
Well, we had an argument

42:59.035 --> 43:01.996
in her apartment,
as you guessed.

43:02.080 --> 43:03.372
About what?

43:03.456 --> 43:05.124
The fact that I was married.

43:05.208 --> 43:07.835
So I was right.

43:07.919 --> 43:10.338
Yes.

43:10.421 --> 43:14.425
But she told me to leave.

43:16.969 --> 43:20.807
It was me
who was begging to stay.

43:20.890 --> 43:22.016
Why?

43:24.102 --> 43:26.354
Have you ever met someone

43:26.437 --> 43:29.649
who‐who looked at you,

43:29.732 --> 43:30.775
all of you,

43:30.858 --> 43:33.152
even the savage parts,

43:33.236 --> 43:34.821
and they didn't flinch?

43:37.073 --> 43:38.825
No.

43:38.908 --> 43:39.867
I thought she was gonna
be the one to bring me back,

43:39.951 --> 43:44.455
restore me to the man I was
before I went to war.

43:44.539 --> 43:45.957
That night

43:46.040 --> 43:48.793
we tried to make love...

43:51.045 --> 43:53.172
...and...

43:53.256 --> 43:55.299
I found that I couldn't.

43:55.383 --> 43:58.469
For years after Afghanistan,

43:58.553 --> 44:02.181
I had thought
the problem was my wife.

44:02.265 --> 44:04.392
But then, all of a sudden,
it was clear.

44:05.643 --> 44:08.104
The problem had been me
all along.

44:10.398 --> 44:13.943
My fate was sealed.

44:14.026 --> 44:17.947
I would never be the man
I was before the war.

44:18.030 --> 44:20.283
And I was never going
to be enough for Alison

44:20.366 --> 44:22.618
or any woman.

44:22.702 --> 44:24.412
So you killed her?

44:26.956 --> 44:30.126
I never felt such rage.

44:30.209 --> 44:31.752
And because Alison
was in front of me,

44:31.836 --> 44:34.255
I‐I directed it at her.

44:34.881 --> 44:38.217
She said she was leaving.

44:38.301 --> 44:40.720
She ran to the door.

44:40.803 --> 44:44.223
And I didn't want her to go,
so I grabbed her by the arm

44:44.307 --> 44:48.227
to try to bring her back,

44:48.311 --> 44:53.065
and I lost my grip,
and she fell, hard,

44:53.149 --> 44:55.818
against the bookshelf.

44:57.570 --> 45:01.199
Before I could reach her,
this statue, a heavy statue,

45:01.282 --> 45:03.868
it fell on her head.

45:05.745 --> 45:08.706
And she was gone.

45:10.416 --> 45:13.711
So... it was an accident?

45:13.794 --> 45:16.547
Yes, of course.

45:16.631 --> 45:19.759
I never wanted
to hurt your mother.

45:32.855 --> 45:36.609
I have... I have tried...

45:36.692 --> 45:40.029
to find a way to make
what I did bearable.

45:40.112 --> 45:44.408
I have dedicated
the last 30 years of my life

45:44.492 --> 45:48.871
creating this place:
a safe haven for veterans.

45:51.624 --> 45:55.336
So nobody again
will ever lose control

45:55.419 --> 45:58.506
the way I did.

45:58.589 --> 46:01.884
Hurt someone the way
I hurt your mother.

46:01.968 --> 46:04.303
You didn't just hurt her.

46:04.387 --> 46:08.057
You killed her.

46:08.140 --> 46:10.851
Yes, and I'm sorry, Joanie.

46:12.728 --> 46:15.648
If you're so sorry, then why
didn't you turn yourself in?

46:15.731 --> 46:18.901
I‐I don't know what good
it would have done.

46:23.197 --> 46:27.451
I‐I‐I could help more people...

46:27.535 --> 46:31.289
make more amends by being
of service to these men,

46:31.372 --> 46:34.333
rather than waste
the rest of my life

46:34.417 --> 46:37.086
rotting away in some cell.

46:37.169 --> 46:39.839
Don't you think you should have
let a jury make that call?

46:40.923 --> 46:44.218
Y‐You know who I think
should make that call?

46:46.137 --> 46:47.054
You.

46:47.138 --> 46:50.808
Me?

46:51.934 --> 46:55.813
I promised myself
a long time ago, Joanie,

46:55.896 --> 46:58.566
that when you found me‐‐

46:58.649 --> 47:03.279
and I knew it was a "when,"
not an "if"‐‐

47:03.362 --> 47:04.238
that I would submit

47:04.322 --> 47:08.993
to whatever accountability
you demanded,

47:09.076 --> 47:12.246
and I‐I‐I would not resist.

47:13.289 --> 47:14.874
So...

47:14.957 --> 47:19.253
if you want to call
the police right now,

47:19.337 --> 47:20.137
I'll give you my phone.

47:23.632 --> 47:27.678
If you want to...
you want to kill me...

47:29.597 --> 47:32.183
...I'll give you my gun.

47:32.266 --> 47:33.976
I am completely in your hands.

47:41.650 --> 47:45.404
If I were going to kill you,

47:45.488 --> 47:48.616
I wouldn't use a gun.

47:48.699 --> 47:50.910
It's too quick.

47:50.993 --> 47:52.411
Okay.

47:52.495 --> 47:55.414
How would you do it?

47:55.498 --> 47:57.750
I'd like to cut off your dick

47:57.833 --> 48:02.713
and let you bleed out
like a pig until you die.

48:05.341 --> 48:09.887
Well... that's an option, too.

48:13.140 --> 48:15.101
I have to go.
I need to think.

48:15.184 --> 48:16.852
Okay, but, Joanie,

48:16.936 --> 48:19.271
you know where to find me now.

48:19.355 --> 48:21.440
And I'm not gonna run.

48:23.192 --> 48:27.154
I'll be right here
whenever you decide.

48:27.238 --> 48:28.948
I have to go.

48:38.499 --> 48:40.459
So, what are you gonna do?

48:40.543 --> 48:41.961
I don't know.

48:42.044 --> 48:45.172
How about calling the police?

48:45.256 --> 48:47.133
I guess I should?

48:48.717 --> 48:49.969
This man murdered your mother

48:50.052 --> 48:51.470
and then sat there and gave you

48:51.554 --> 48:53.389
a detailed description
of how he did it.

48:53.472 --> 48:56.684
That's a special kind
of psychopath.

48:56.767 --> 48:58.477
He's a lot of things,
but I‐I don't think

48:58.561 --> 49:01.021
he's a psychopath.

49:03.774 --> 49:05.151
What?

49:05.234 --> 49:09.655
He seemed sorry.

49:09.738 --> 49:13.367
Truly sorry.

49:13.451 --> 49:16.328
He spent his entire life
trying to make amends.

49:16.412 --> 49:18.664
Uh, Joanie, most murderers
are sorry for what they did.

49:18.747 --> 49:20.207
They still have to go to prison.

49:20.291 --> 49:22.001
He said I could kill him
if I liked.

49:22.084 --> 49:24.044
I think that would be a mistake.

49:24.128 --> 49:25.171
I wasn't being serious.

49:25.254 --> 49:26.213
‐Yes, you were.
‐No, I wasn't.

49:26.297 --> 49:27.339
I think you were.

49:27.423 --> 49:30.259
‐EJ.
‐Joanie, listen to me.

49:30.342 --> 49:31.844
This problem is
above your pay grade.

49:31.927 --> 49:33.304
There are people who specialize

49:33.387 --> 49:35.264
in crime and punishment
for a living.

49:35.347 --> 49:36.891
That's why they're called
the authorities.

49:36.974 --> 49:38.017
How about we let them
decide what to do

49:38.100 --> 49:41.395
before we take vengeance
into our own hands.

49:41.479 --> 49:45.191
Ben may be sorry, but he was
clearheaded enough at the time

49:45.274 --> 49:47.026
to use your mother's history
of mental illness against her

49:47.109 --> 49:50.404
and make everyone believe
she drowned herself.

49:55.284 --> 49:57.161
That's right.

49:57.661 --> 50:01.373
She drowned.

50:01.457 --> 50:04.126
They found water in her lungs.

50:35.491 --> 50:36.992
Benjamin Cruz?

50:37.076 --> 50:39.245
Can I help you?

50:39.328 --> 50:41.580
I'm Detective Clark,
this is Detective Woods.

50:41.664 --> 50:42.581
We'd like to ask you
a few questions

50:42.665 --> 50:44.625
pertaining to the death
of Alison Bailey.

50:44.708 --> 50:45.709
May we come in?

50:45.793 --> 50:48.212
I've made my decision.

50:51.173 --> 50:52.591
Where did you find her?

50:54.176 --> 50:56.345
She's one of the patients
from my facility.

50:56.428 --> 51:00.724
She went AWOL last night...
and we've been worried sick.

51:00.808 --> 51:03.310
What?

51:03.394 --> 51:05.145
This is her signature,
committing herself

51:05.229 --> 51:07.147
‐to psychiatric care.
‐What?

51:07.231 --> 51:08.899
And this is my case study
for Joanie Lockhart.

51:08.983 --> 51:11.277
She was admitted
three weeks ago.

51:11.360 --> 51:12.444
That's not true.
None of this is true.

51:12.528 --> 51:14.363
Joanie suffers from severe
depression and PTSD.

51:14.446 --> 51:15.948
Her mother tragically
committed suicide

51:16.031 --> 51:18.158
when she was seven years old.

51:18.242 --> 51:21.412
And lately she's been
experiencing homicidal

51:21.495 --> 51:22.496
fantasies and delusions.

51:22.580 --> 51:23.998
‐This is all horseshit.
‐We have been exploring

51:24.081 --> 51:27.001
some of them in a safe,
therapeutic space,

51:27.084 --> 51:29.795
but, um, yesterday
she had a turn for the worse

51:29.878 --> 51:32.881
and she threatened my life.

51:35.551 --> 51:37.303
<i>I'd like to cut off your dick</i>

51:37.386 --> 51:40.806
<i>and let you bleed out
like a pig until you die.</i>

51:40.889 --> 51:42.141
That is not what I said.

51:42.224 --> 51:44.268
That isn't your voice
on the recording?

51:44.351 --> 51:45.978
Of course it is, but it was
meant as a hypothetical,

51:46.061 --> 51:48.314
like... if I <i>were</i> to kill him.

51:51.442 --> 51:54.028
He knew my mother. He isn't just
a random doctor I came to see.

51:54.111 --> 51:57.531
He was dating her when she died.

51:57.615 --> 51:59.658
He told me that he set up
this whole clinic

51:59.742 --> 52:02.411
because he felt like such a shit
for what he did 30 years ago.

52:02.494 --> 52:03.829
Officers,
I have nothing to hide.

52:03.912 --> 52:06.373
I was cleared of any wrongdoing

52:06.457 --> 52:08.375
in Alison Bailey's death
years ago.

52:08.459 --> 52:10.711
The police ruled it
as a suicide.

52:10.794 --> 52:11.879
Joanie just can't accept it.

52:11.962 --> 52:15.341
She needs someone to blame.

52:15.424 --> 52:20.346
She herself has made
a series of suicide attempts,

52:20.429 --> 52:23.891
as you can see referenced
on pages five and six.

52:25.392 --> 52:28.312
Ms. Lockhart,
what are you doing?

52:28.395 --> 52:30.397
Where is it, Ben?

52:30.481 --> 52:32.650
‐Where's your fucking gun?
‐There's no gun.

52:32.733 --> 52:34.526
He said I could kill him with it
if I wanted to.

52:34.610 --> 52:35.944
I don't have a gun, Joanie.

52:36.028 --> 52:37.780
I run a therapeutic center

52:37.863 --> 52:40.032
for PTSD recovery.

52:40.115 --> 52:42.701
A gun would be
a very dangerous thing

52:42.785 --> 52:45.371
to have on these premises,
wouldn't it?

52:45.454 --> 52:47.164
Ms. Lockhart,
is it true what he's saying?

52:47.247 --> 52:49.875
Are you a patient
at this facility?

52:49.958 --> 52:52.711
- ‐No, of course not.
- ‐ All right, but...

52:52.795 --> 52:54.213
this is your signature
on this form?

52:54.296 --> 52:57.049
I wasn't paying attention
to what I was signing.

52:57.132 --> 53:00.219
So you didn't read
what the form said?

53:00.302 --> 53:02.388
You aren't listening to me.

53:02.471 --> 53:04.390
I'm telling the truth.

53:04.473 --> 53:05.273
I'm not the crazy one.

53:05.349 --> 53:08.268
‐He is.
‐Okay, well, why would you sign

53:08.352 --> 53:09.728
something you didn't read,
ma'am?

53:09.812 --> 53:10.896
Because I was too busy
thinking about

53:10.979 --> 53:11.779
how I was gonna kill him.

53:14.650 --> 53:16.610
Mr. Cruz, do you want us

53:16.694 --> 53:18.404
to remove Ms. Lockhart
from the property?

53:18.487 --> 53:20.447
That won't be necessary.

53:20.531 --> 53:22.199
Are you sure, sir?

53:22.282 --> 53:25.411
More than anything, right now,
she needs my support.

53:25.494 --> 53:28.247
Sorry to have wasted
your time, Officers.

53:28.330 --> 53:29.498
Okay.

53:41.385 --> 53:44.596
I'm gonna fucking kill you.

53:44.680 --> 53:46.932
You can't touch me now, Joanie.

53:47.015 --> 53:51.061
Police are watching you now.

53:51.145 --> 53:53.856
You'll go to prison
for the rest of your life.

53:53.939 --> 53:56.316
Your kids will grow up
without a mother.

53:56.400 --> 53:58.402
That's not what you want, is it?

53:58.485 --> 54:00.612
What do you know about my kids?

54:00.696 --> 54:01.864
I meant what I said.

54:01.947 --> 54:06.452
I thought about you over the
years, wondered how you were.

54:06.535 --> 54:08.954
Were you watching me?

54:09.037 --> 54:11.123
I looked you up online.

54:11.206 --> 54:12.124
When did you know it was me?

54:12.207 --> 54:15.961
When you took off
your sunglasses.

54:16.044 --> 54:17.504
Why didn't you say
something then?

54:17.588 --> 54:20.132
What was the point
of this whole exercise?

54:23.719 --> 54:25.763
My mother was still breathing

54:25.846 --> 54:28.182
when her body
went into the water.

54:28.265 --> 54:30.434
She didn't die in our apartment
like you said she did.

54:30.517 --> 54:32.644
She had water in her lungs.

54:32.728 --> 54:34.480
She fucking drowned.

54:34.563 --> 54:35.272
Calm down.

54:35.355 --> 54:38.358
Can I get you something?
A drink?

54:38.442 --> 54:40.152
You wanted me
to call the police.

54:40.235 --> 54:41.487
So you could show them
my signature

54:41.570 --> 54:45.782
and play them the tape
and make me seem like a nutjob.

54:45.866 --> 54:49.161
The one person left alive
who knows what you did.

54:49.244 --> 54:50.496
You killed her, and then you
dumped her body in the water.

54:50.579 --> 54:53.749
You made it look like a suicide.
You used her history

54:53.832 --> 54:57.127
and you set her up just like you
set me up, didn't you?

54:59.004 --> 55:00.088
Yes.

55:00.172 --> 55:02.299
Why?

55:02.382 --> 55:03.717
I didn't want to go to prison.

55:03.800 --> 55:06.011
Oh, you're a killer.
You belong in prison.

55:06.094 --> 55:08.722
Oh, thou shall not kill.

55:08.805 --> 55:12.309
Well... except sometimes.

55:12.392 --> 55:14.186
I killed people in Afghanistan,
plenty of them.

55:14.269 --> 55:17.814
Some of them innocent civilians.

55:19.149 --> 55:21.193
It wasn't a crime there.

55:21.276 --> 55:23.529
Why should it be a crime here?

55:24.738 --> 55:28.158
You took my mother from me.

55:30.035 --> 55:31.495
I was a child.

55:34.456 --> 55:35.541
You took her.

55:41.571 --> 55:42.371
You know,

55:42.381 --> 55:45.884
you are just so much like her.

55:45.968 --> 55:47.886
When you showed up at my door,

55:47.970 --> 55:52.099
you seemed so...
strong, so tough.

55:53.267 --> 55:56.270
I should have known
it was a mask.

55:56.353 --> 55:58.063
Just like hers.

55:58.146 --> 55:59.189
You're just as sad

55:59.273 --> 56:01.817
and as frightened as she was.

56:21.003 --> 56:22.963
Harder.

56:23.046 --> 56:24.673
Harder.

56:24.756 --> 56:27.593
Oh.

56:29.428 --> 56:34.266
I understand
why you came here now.

56:34.349 --> 56:37.394
It wasn't for Alison at all.

56:38.895 --> 56:42.774
You just want someone
to put you out of your pain.

56:46.820 --> 56:50.490
I'm not gonna do you that favor.

56:56.288 --> 56:59.791
I'm sorry for your pain, Joanie.

56:59.875 --> 57:02.753
I really am.

57:04.671 --> 57:07.966
But if I go away,

57:08.050 --> 57:10.802
what happens to these patients?

57:10.886 --> 57:12.763
They need me here.

57:12.846 --> 57:16.642
You are so full of shit,
and you know it.

57:16.725 --> 57:18.602
I've paid for my sins.

57:20.270 --> 57:23.982
I can live with myself.

57:28.695 --> 57:31.865
You're the one, apparently,

57:31.948 --> 57:34.076
who cannot.

